 temper with passions not strong only but noble and of the sort in which great virtues and great poems take their rise it is his love towards his country people and nature that inspires him that opens his eyes to its beauty leading his heart and voice to praise them with his passion robert burns was born january   in a strawthatched cottage to william and agnes burns his mother had a great store of folklore songs and ballads and his father tried at all costs to surround his children with good reading and conversation at the age of seven his father moved the family to from alloway in  at the age of only  robert composed his first song handsome nell in honor of the village blacksmiths daughter read more comments  you must sign in to make a comment robert burnshelperatsof trouble downloading copyright complaint buy now  usd buy with paypal instant download moneyback guarantee buy with  download creditsyou have  credits earn credits h helperatsof dgoodz message helperatsof message helperatsof send file send message   helperatsof wwwdgoodzcomuserhelperatsof rating published onprint length pagesword count  file namerobertburnsrtf file size kb  mb sold byhelperatsof purchased times best seller ranking other items from helperatsof customers also bought view all customers also viewed view all burns by robert burns hardcover  barnes  noble®  off the criterion collection   favorite paperbacks buy  get the rd free   back to school for all ages   top books of the month   membership gift cards stores  events help bnlogo auto suggestions are available once you type at least  letters use up and down arrow to review and enter to select allbooksnook booksnooktextbooksbargain booksnewsstandteenskidstoys  gameshobbies  collectibleshome  giftsmovies  tvmusic items in your shopping bag click to view the items in your shopping bag you have × uhoh it looks like your internet explorer is out of date for a better shopping experience please upgrade now    javascript is not enabled in your bro